2004-08-25 19:25  Stephen Bach <sjbach@users.sourceforge.net>

	* glob-expand.c:
	  If a file argument has a trailing '/', it is also treated as a directory,
	  i.e. it will show a listing for that directory if valid.  This way you
	  can see the contents of a directory in gviewglob without referencing
	  a file in that directory first.  Idea submitted by Pavel Tavoda.

